---
import Sprite from 'astro-icon';
import TechCard from '../components/TechCard.astro';
import Container from '../components/Container.astro';
---

<Container as="section">
  <div class="tech-grid">
    <TechCard title="Nuxt">
      <svg
        aria-hidden="true"
        slot="icon"
        viewBox="0 0 135 90"
        fill="none"
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
        data-v-693c3d67=""
      >
        <title>Nuxt logo</title>
        <path
          d="M74.2284 87.8731H123.414C124.977 87.8733 126.511 87.4745 127.864 86.7167C129.217 85.959 130.341 84.869 131.121 83.5565C131.902 82.244 132.313 80.7552 132.312 79.2398C132.312 77.7245 131.899 76.2361 131.118 74.9242L98.0856 19.4276C97.3048 18.1154 96.1817 17.0257 94.829 16.2681C93.4764 15.5105 91.942 15.1116 90.38 15.1116C88.8181 15.1116 87.2836 15.5105 85.931 16.2681C84.5784 17.0257 83.4552 18.1154 82.6745 19.4276L74.2284 33.6272L57.7148 5.86031C56.9334 4.54821 55.8097 3.45868 54.4567 2.70119C53.1037 1.9437 51.569 1.54492 50.0068 1.54492C48.4446 1.54492 46.9099 1.9437 45.5569 2.70119C44.2039 3.45868 43.0803 4.54821 42.2989 5.86031L1.1947 74.9242C0.41273 76.2361 0.000680577 77.7245 8.42355e-07 79.2398C-0.000678893 80.7552 0.410035 82.244 1.19083 83.5565C1.97163 84.869 3.09498 85.959 4.44789 86.7167C5.80081 87.4745 7.33558 87.8733 8.89785 87.8731H39.7727C52.0057 87.8731 61.0271 82.661 67.2346 72.4925L82.3054 47.1759L90.3776 33.6272L114.604 74.3244H82.3054L74.2284 87.8731ZM39.2694 74.3105L17.7227 74.3058L50.0212 20.046L66.1369 47.1759L55.3468 65.309C51.2244 71.9067 46.5411 74.3105 39.2694 74.3105Z"
          fill="#00DC82"
        >
        </path>
      </svg>

      <Fragment slot="description">
        Nuxt 3 has redefined what peak DX means. Offering a stellar approach to
        full stack development on top of VueJS, we believe it's the best way to
        deliver high value as fast as possible.
      </Fragment>
    </TechCard>
    <TechCard title="TypeScript">
      <svg
        aria-hidden="true"
        slot="icon"
        version="1.1"
        viewBox="0 0 512 512"
        class="aspect-square h-10 py-1"
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
      >
        <title>TypeScript</title>
        <rect width="512" height="512" rx="50" fill="#3178c6"></rect>
        <path
          d="m317 407v50c8.1 4.2 18 7.3 29 9.4s23 3.1 35 3.1c12 0 23-1.1 34-3.4 11-2.3 20-6.1 28-11 8.1-5.3 15-12 19-21s7.1-19 7.1-32c0-9.1-1.4-17-4.1-24s-6.6-13-12-18c-5.1-5.3-11-10-18-14s-15-8.2-24-12c-6.6-2.7-12-5.3-18-7.9-5.2-2.6-9.7-5.2-13-7.8-3.7-2.7-6.5-5.5-8.5-8.4-2-3-3-6.3-3-10 0-3.4 0.89-6.5 2.7-9.3s4.3-5.1 7.5-7.1c3.2-2 7.2-3.5 12-4.6 4.7-1.1 9.9-1.6 16-1.6 4.2 0 8.6 0.31 13 0.94 4.6 0.63 9.3 1.6 14 2.9 4.7 1.3 9.3 2.9 14 4.9 4.4 2 8.5 4.3 12 6.9v-47c-7.6-2.9-16-5.1-25-6.5s-19-2.1-31-2.1c-12 0-23 1.3-34 3.8s-20 6.5-28 12c-8.1 5.4-14 12-19 21-4.7 8.4-7 18-7 30 0 15 4.3 28 13 38 8.6 11 22 19 39 27 6.9 2.8 13 5.6 19 8.3s11 5.5 15 8.4c4.3 2.9 7.7 6.1 10 9.5 2.5 3.4 3.8 7.4 3.8 12 0 3.2-0.78 6.2-2.3 9s-3.9 5.2-7.1 7.2-7.1 3.6-12 4.8c-4.7 1.1-10 1.7-17 1.7-11 0-22-1.9-32-5.7-11-3.8-21-9.5-30-17zm-84-123h64v-41h-179v41h64v183h51z"
          clip-rule="evenodd"
          fill="#fff"
          fill-rule="evenodd"
          style="fill:#fff"
        >
        </path>
      </svg>

      <Fragment slot="description">
        Over the years, TypeScript has grown to become the industry standard,
        and it's very well deserve. The type safety is the tip ot the iceberg;
        TS is a great tool to make you feel in control of your code.
      </Fragment>
    </TechCard>
    <TechCard title="tRPC">
      <svg
        slot="icon"
        aria-hidden="true"
        viewBox="0 0 512 512"
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
        class="aspect-square h-10 fill-[#398CCB] py-1"
      >
        <title>tRPC</title>
        <rect width="512" height="512" rx="150" fill="#398CCB"></rect>
        <path
          fill-rule="evenodd"
          clip-rule="evenodd"
          d="M255.446 75L326.523 116.008V138.556L412.554 188.238V273.224L435.631 286.546V368.608L364.6 409.615L333.065 391.378L256.392 435.646L180.178 391.634L149.085 409.615L78.0538 368.538V286.546L100.231 273.743V188.238L184.415 139.638L184.462 139.636V116.008L255.446 75ZM326.523 159.879V198.023L255.492 239.031L184.462 198.023V160.936L184.415 160.938L118.692 198.9V263.084L149.085 245.538L220.115 286.546V368.538L198.626 380.965L256.392 414.323L314.618 380.712L293.569 368.538V286.546L364.6 245.538L394.092 262.565V198.9L326.523 159.879ZM312.031 357.969V307.915L355.369 332.931V382.985L312.031 357.969ZM417.169 307.846L373.831 332.862V382.985L417.169 357.9V307.846ZM96.5154 357.9V307.846L139.854 332.862V382.915L96.5154 357.9ZM201.654 307.846L158.315 332.862V382.915L201.654 357.9V307.846ZM321.262 291.923L364.6 266.908L407.938 291.923L364.6 316.962L321.262 291.923ZM149.085 266.838L105.746 291.923L149.085 316.892L192.423 291.923L149.085 266.838ZM202.923 187.362V137.308L246.215 162.346V212.377L202.923 187.362ZM308.015 137.308L264.723 162.346V212.354L308.015 187.362V137.308ZM212.154 121.338L255.446 96.3231L298.785 121.338L255.446 146.354L212.154 121.338Z"
          fill="white"
        >
        </path>
      </svg>

      <Fragment slot="description">
        If your frontend and backend are TypeScript, it's really hard to beat
        the DX of tRPC. Kinda like GraphQL but without the work - seriously this
        lib is magic.
      </Fragment>
    </TechCard>
    <TechCard title="Vue-query">
      <svg
        slot="icon"
        aria-hidden="true"
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
        width="100px"
        height="100px"
        viewBox="0 0 261.76 226.69"
      >
        <path
          fill="#ffd94c"
          stroke="#002c4b"
          stroke-width="32.63"
          d="M156.77 42.75L126.55 95.1 96.32 42.75h-48.3l78.53 136 78.53-136z"
        >
        </path>
        <path
          fill="none"
          stroke="#ff4154"
          stroke-width="12.43"
          d="M156.77 42.75L126.55 95.1 96.32 42.75h-48.3l78.53 136 78.53-136z"
        >
        </path>
      </svg>

      <Fragment slot="description">
        The Vue adapter of Tanstack Query is an amazing tool to manage the
        server side state of your application. The granularity it offers while
        at the same time making your life easier makes it an auto-include in any
        front end project.
      </Fragment>
    </TechCard>
    <TechCard title="Prisma">
      <svg
        slot="icon"
        aria-hidden="true"
        role="img"
        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
        class="prisma-logo"
      >
        <title>Prisma</title>
        <path
          d="M21.8068 18.2848L13.5528.7565c-.207-.4382-.639-.7273-1.1286-.7541-.5023-.0293-.9523.213-1.2062.6253L2.266 15.1271c-.2773.4518-.2718 1.0091.0158 1.4555l4.3759 6.7786c.2608.4046.7127.6388 1.1823.6388.1332 0 .267-.0188.3987-.0577l12.7019-3.7568c.3891-.1151.7072-.3904.8737-.7553s.1633-.7828-.0075-1.1454zm-1.8481.7519L9.1814 22.2242c-.3292.0975-.6448-.1873-.5756-.5194l3.8501-18.4386c.072-.3448.5486-.3996.699-.0803l7.1288 15.138c.1344.2856-.019.6224-.325.7128z"
        >
        </path>
      </svg>

      <Fragment slot="description">
        Finding a quality database ORM in the TypeScript ecosystem is no easy
        feat. Prisma fits the bill with flying colors. Just define your schema
        and query away, no matter your SQL dialect, or even MongoDB.
      </Fragment>
    </TechCard>
    <TechCard title="Open Props Style">
      <svg aria-hidden="true" slot="icon" viewBox="0 0 200 200">
        <line
          stroke="#bac8ff"
          x1="66"
          x2="66"
          y1="100"
          y2="175"
          stroke-width="25"
        >
        </line>
        <circle
          stroke="#bac8ff"
          cx="100"
          cy="100"
          r="35"
          fill="transparent"
          stroke-width="25"
        >
        </circle>
        <circle
          stroke="#748ffc"
          cx="100"
          cy="100"
          r="85"
          fill="transparent"
          stroke-width="25"
        >
        </circle>
      </svg>

      <Fragment slot="description">
        CSS Variables completely changed the way we write modern CSS. Open Props
        provides you with a sensible and exhaustive set of design tokens to help
        you easily craft consistent and responsive components.
      </Fragment>
    </TechCard>
    <TechCard title="Auth.js">
      <img
        aria-hidden="true"
        src="/images/nextauth.webp"
        slot="icon"
        alt="NextAuth.js"
      />

      <Fragment slot="description">
        Auth.js fast tracks you to building flexible and secure authentication.
        It ties into your existing database and provides a simple API to manage
        users and sessions.
      </Fragment>
    </TechCard>
    <TechCard title="Vue-i18n">
      <img
        aria-hidden="true"
        src="/images/vue-i18n-logo.png"
        slot="icon"
        alt="Vue-18n"
      />

      <Fragment slot="description">
        The de facto solution to internationalize your Vue application. Its nuxt
        plugin helps you seamlessly build your application with multiple
        languages in mind.
      </Fragment>
    </TechCard>
    <TechCard title="...and more">
      <Sprite name="mdi:hammer-wrench" aria-hidden="true" slot="icon" />

      <Fragment slot="description">
        Create V3 App comes with a lot of great Nuxt modules to solve common
        problems like a nuxt-typed-router, nuxt-icons, and nuxt-color-mode.
      </Fragment>
    </TechCard>
  </div>
</Container>

<style>
  @import 'open-props/media';

  .tech-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(30ch, 1fr));
    column-gap: var(--size-3);
    row-gap: var(--size-5);

    & svg,
    img {
      width: 2rem;
      aspect-ratio: 1;
    }
  }

  @media (--OSdark) {
    .prisma-logo {
      fill: white;
    }
  }
</style>
